node.text: For those of you wanting to know what happened when/how Knox was born ❤️ So I went into labor at 3am Jan 6th my plan was to birth at home since we had an amazing home birth with my last... I called midwifes about 4:30am and they got there about an hour later I labored at home until about 11:30am at that point I was 8cm and was there for a while broke my water and after that I felt like I had to push... my body wasn’t ready but I couldn’t help the feeling of pushing. Everything just felt so off contractions everything just didn’t feel right. We got to the hospital I waited about an hour to get my epidural, my thought was the epidural would help me not want to push because at this point my cervix was swelling and going back in dilation... So once they started monitoring baby his heart rate kept dropping super low after each contraction which... after trying everything from stoping contractions to changing positions he still wasn’t handling them well. My body wasn’t fully dilating which is strange since I’ve already had two births.. I was stuck at 9 cm for hours.. she checked me one last time and said she would try and let me push at 9cm so we did.. he was in the sunny side up position and not budging at all.. so at that point I knew it was time he needed to come out. It was time for a c-section. I am so thankful for everyone that made this all happen! At 6:15pm he came out and that’s when we found out it was a big 8.15 lb boy!! After that everyone in the room said do you see the knot in that cord!!! So he had a big knot in his cord which sometimes can be no problem but also sometimes can get pulled during labor and it only takes a minute to cut off oxygen to the brain. We are so blessed that the Lord was watching over us and we were able to get done what needed to and me and baby were safe and so blessed! I feel for all you mamas that have to have that done every time! The healing process is terrible! Big thank you for all the love and the prayers! We are doing great he is already back up past birth weight and perfect! ♥️

node.text: This year has been hard for me losing two people very dear to me. The holidays make things a little better and a little worse... worse because you just miss them being around all of your family and they’re not there but also better because you get to be around the family that also misses them, and will cry with you, make you laugh and remember the good times you had with them. Be thankful for what you have in your life, you never know how long it’s suppose to be there 💙💜 Also reach out to people you never know how they are feeling they might need a text/call from you. If you are struggling please reach out you have so many people in your life that care and love you ❤️

node.text: Travel days!!! I miss the kids more than anything!! But so thankful that we get to travel together!! About 7 years ago Roman had to travel without me. I would stay home with the boys while he came to LA or wherever he needed to be. This was for a few years we would miss each other like crazy but it’s what we had to do to get to where we are today! Love this man so much it’s about to be our 11 year anniversary 😵🥰
